Class Billet

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.cf.milling.objects.Billet
public class Billet extends Object

  • Constructor Details

    • Billet

      public Billet​(int billetId, String billetName, int billetShape, int materialId, double xBilletMin, double xBilletMax, double yBilletMin, double yBilletMax, double zBilletMin, double zBilletMax)
      Billet constructor does not generate a mesh therefore part remains null.
      Parameters:
      billetId - - id and primary key for billet entry in the database
      billetName - - name to show for this billet
      billetShape - - shape of the billet (rectangle, cylinder, complex)
      materialId - - id of the material that this billet is made of
      xBilletMin - - min X coordinate of total billet volume when placed on table
      xBilletMax - - max X coordinate of total billet volume when placed on table
      yBilletMin - - min Y coordinate of total billet volume when placed on table
      yBilletMax - - max Y coordinate of total billet volume when placed on table
      zBilletMin - - min Z coordinate of total billet volume when placed on table
      zBilletMax - - max Z coordinate of total billet volume when placed on table

    • Billet

      public Billet​(String billetName, List<Billet> primaryBillets, int materialId)
      Constructor of a complex billet from primary billets with mesh
      Parameters:
      billetName - - The name of the generated complex billet, different from its elements
      primaryBillets - - A List of billets to combine and create the complex
      materialId - - The material of the billet independent of the materials of its elements
